FBIS4-48517 "drafr098_c_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Public Servants Group Warns of `Unrest' Over Pay Problems Public Servants Group Warns of `Unrest' Over Pay Problems MB2005092794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 20 May 94 MB2005092794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The Public Servants Association of South Africa has warned that serious unrest could result from the nonpayment of special danger allowances promised to Correctional Services personnel over the election period. The newly-appointed general manager of the association, Mr. Casper van Rensburg, said the association would take all the necessary steps to ensure that its Correctional Services members were paid the special allowance which was granted to other uniformed personnel.
